not only abjure all kinds of meat and eggs, they also refuse to eat onions, potatoes or anything grown under the soil. even meat-eating hindus often follow special diets during religious days or during fasts. hindu fasts do not involve giving up all food, just eating a restricted diet — some take only fruits. a very small group of indians are, or used to be piscatarians — i.e. they count fish as a vegetable product. among these are bengali and konkani brahmins. such people are increasingly rare as most have taken to meat-eating. visiting vegetarians will discover a culinary treasure 